        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "A five-minute nighttime tapping practice from Day 26 of a 30-day sleep intensive. The script targets the not-enough-done pattern: lying down but unable to stop, the mind still running the list of things left. The reframe moves toward the specific felt experience of permission, the exhale of 'done enough, safe to stop'.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "New to tapping? Read ",
